Removes the customer-session login guard added at the top of
Cinovo\Buyorder\Helper\BuyorderHelper::getContactPaymentConnections in
cinovo/buyorder 2.6.9.

Root cause: getContactPaymentConnections is shared between the storefront and
the admin panel (e.g. Cinovo\Bankaccount\Controller\Adminhtml\Bankaccount\GetBankAccounts).
The guard checks Magento\Customer\Model\Session::isLoggedIn(), which is never
logged in in the adminhtml area, so the method always returns null and the
admin bank-account lookup is broken.

Fix: comment out the guard so the method works in every area again. The
storefront-only "return null when the customer is not logged in" behaviour is
restored via an around plugin scoped to the frontend area in
creativestyle/customization-proaurum-cinovo
(Plugin/Cinovo/Buyorder/Helper/BuyorderHelper/ReturnNullWhenCustomerNotLoggedIn),
so the storefront contract is unchanged while the admin flow is fixed.

